.TH ARX 1 "2025-11-22" "arx 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
arx \- Archive eXtractor - unified archive management tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B arx
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIfile1\fR [\fIfile2\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B arx
is a user-friendly wrapper around tar, gzip, bzip2, xz, zstd, zip, and 7z that provides a unified interface for archive compression, extraction, and listing operations.

It automatically detects archive formats, provides helpful error messages, supports pattern filtering, and includes advanced features like verification and progress display.

.SH MODES
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-compress \fIFORMAT\fR
Compress files into archive. FORMAT can be:
.br
tar, tar.gz (tgz), tar.bz2 (tbz2), tar.xz (txz), tar.zst, zip, 7z
.TP
.B \-x, \-\-extract
Extract archive (default mode if archive file specified)
.TP
.B \-l, \-\-list
List contents of archive

.SH GENERAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-target \fIDIR\fR
Target directory for extraction (default: current directory)
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-name \fINAME\fR
Archive name without extension (for compression)
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Suppress output (quiet mode)
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-delete
Delete original files after successful operation
.TP
.B \-\-verify
Verify archive integrity after compression
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Preview operation without executing
.TP
.B \-\-no\-confirm
Skip confirmation prompts (for automation)
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable debug trace output
.TP
.B \-\-version
Display version information
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message

.SH COMPRESSION OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-L, \-\-level \fIN\fR
Compression level: 0-9 for most formats, 1-22 for zstd
.br
0 = fastest/least compression
.br
9 = slowest/best compression
.TP
.B \-j, \-\-jobs \fIN\fR
Number of parallel threads for compression
.TP
.B \-e, \-\-exclude \fIPATTERN\fR
Exclude files matching glob pattern (can be used multiple times)
.TP
.B \-i, \-\-include \fIPATTERN\fR
Include only files matching glob pattern (can be used multiple times)
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-filter \fIFILE\fR
Load include/exclude patterns from file
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-password
Prompt for password (zip and 7z only)
.TP
.B \-\-allow\-insecure\-password
Allow password to be visible in process list (required with \-p)

.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic Compression
.TP
Compress a single file:
.B arx \-c tar.gz \-n archive file.txt
.TP
Compress multiple files:
.B arx \-c zip \-n backup file1.txt file2.txt
.TP
Compress entire directory:
.B arx \-c tar.xz \-n project project_folder/

.SS Advanced Compression
.TP
Compress with verification:
.B arx \-c tar.gz \-n important \-\-verify data/
.TP
Compress with maximum compression:
.B arx \-c tar.xz \-L 9 \-n small largefile.dat
.TP
Compress using 8 threads:
.B arx \-c tar.xz \-j 8 \-n fast big_directory/
.TP
Compress excluding patterns:
.B arx \-c tar.gz \-n code \-e "*.o" \-e "*.tmp" project/
.TP
Compress with password:
.B arx \-c zip \-n secure \-p \-\-allow\-insecure\-password secret/

.SS Extraction
.TP
Extract to current directory:
.B arx archive.tar.gz
.TP
Extract to specific directory:
.B arx \-t /opt/extracted archive.zip
.TP
Extract and delete archive:
.B arx \-d old_backup.tar.gz

.SS Listing
.TP
List archive contents:
.B arx \-l archive.tar.gz
.TP
List multiple archives:
.B arx \-l *.zip

.SH FILE PATTERNS
Pattern matching uses glob syntax:
.TP
.B *
Matches any characters
.TP
.B ?
Matches single character
.TP
.B [abc]
Matches a, b, or c
.TP
.B [!abc]
Matches any character except a, b, or c

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error (file not found, operation failed, etc.)
.TP
.B 2
Help displayed (not an error)
.TP
.B 3
Version displayed (not an error)
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by user (Ctrl+C)

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ARX_SCRIPT
Path to arx.sh script (used by test suite)

.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.bashrc
Source arx.sh here for bash completion

.SH NOTES
.SS Supported Formats
.TP
.B tar
Uncompressed tar archive
.TP
.B tar.gz (tgz)
Tar archive compressed with gzip (fast, good compatibility)
.TP
.B tar.bz2 (tbz2)
Tar archive compressed with bzip2 (better ratio than gzip)
.TP
.B tar.xz (txz)
Tar archive compressed with xz (best ratio, recommended)
.TP
.B tar.zst
Tar archive compressed with zstd (fast with good ratio, modern)
.TP
.B zip
ZIP archive (universal compatibility)
.TP
.B 7z
7-Zip archive (excellent compression)

.SS Dependencies
Required: bash 4.4+, tar
.br
For specific formats: gzip, bzip2, xz, zstd, zip, 7z
.br
Optional: pv (for progress display)

.SS Security Considerations
.IP \(bu 2
Passwords are stored in memory and visible in process list
.IP \(bu 2
Use
.B \-p
for interactive password entry (more secure)
.IP \(bu 2
Symbolic links are preserved but not validated
.IP \(bu 2
Archives use relative paths (no leading /)

.SS Performance Tips
.IP \(bu 2
Use tar.zst for balanced speed and compression
.IP \(bu 2
Use tar.xz \-L 9 for maximum compression
.IP \(bu 2
Use
.B \-j
for parallel compression on multi-core systems
.IP \(bu 2
Use \-\-verify for critical data integrity

